array.name: syste_error_choose
array.item: 1. The ignition switch is in keyII or keyIII position or the engine is started
2. The diagnostic connector is properly connected and extension cord has been used
3. Vehicle battery voltage and communication pin voltage are normal
4. The vehicle is equipped with the system
5. The ECU fuse and ECU line are normal
6. The ignition switch has been turned off and turned on again
7. The VCI has been disconnected and connected again, or the host device has been restarted
8. Lines related to the ECU and OBD are not original.
9. The vehicle is not equipped with the OBD-related car model
10. The bus switch is on if it is available

Bluetooth connection attempt failed many times, please try the following suggestion:

 1. Check whether the bluetooth connection has been powered on or near the effective distance (10 meters).

 2. If the bluetooth connector is used with other equipment,please enter the other equipment and open the system Settings program, switch to the Bluetooth item, unpair the bluetooth connector, go back to current equipment Diagnostic application to pair and connect the connector again.

 3. Otherwise,open the system Settings program, switch to the Bluetooth item, unpair the VCI, go back to Diagnostic application to pair and connect the VCI again.

 4. Restart the host, enter into the diagnostic application system to reconnect.

This step is to connect device to printer hotspot. 
 When the printer is ON, click [Scan] button at upper right corner to search printer hotspot. Hotspot name format is: X-431 PRINTER-XXXX.
 If printer hotspot not found, click [Refresh] button to retry or check below:
 1.Whether printer is powered on
 2.Whether printer has been configured.
 If the printer has been configured, it will convert to LAN mode and lost its own Wi-Fi hotspot. Only resetting can recover its own Wi-Fi hotspot.

 Printer resetting method: 
 Press and hold MODE and FEED buttons at the same time for approx 5sec. When POWER indicator flashes, release the buttons. Then press the MODE button, the printer will show below messages: 
 1. The WIFI not responding temporarily, may is being rebooted, please try again later. (indicate resetting failed)
 2. at+default=1
 ok
 at+reboot=1
 rebooting
 (indicate resetting succeeded)

This step is to connect both the printer and this device to the selected LAN.

 Note:

Welcome to use the Launch Wi-Fi printer, please finish configuration as follows before using.

 [Step 1]: Connect this unit to the printer Wi-Fi directly, which name like X-431PRINTER-XXX, default password is 12345678. When connected, go next step.

 [Step 2]: Select the Wi-Fi network to which the printer will connect, including Wi-Fi name, password, then save and go next step. Make sure the Wi-Fi network is active.

 [Step 3]: This unit will also connect to the Wi-Fi network automatically, then click Search Printer button, when found the printer, printer configuration is done.

 Reset printer：
 * Hold down the FEED and MODE button for 3 seconds to print the Wi-Fi configuration.
 * Hold down the FEED and MODE button for 10 seconds to restore the Wi-Fi to factory default.
